Title : Amir Yacoby
Text : '''Amir Yacoby''' is a condensed matter physicist and a professor at [[Harvard University]]. In 1994 he obtained his PhD at [[Weizmann Institute of Science]], and was appointed as the Lazaridis Chair in Physics of [[Institute for Quantum Computing]] in 2013.<ref>[http://www.newswire.ca/en/story/1226989/institute-for-quantum-computing-adds-former-csa-chief-harvard-professor Institute for Quantum Computing adds former CSA chief, Harvard professor]</ref> In March 2014, his group developed a [[magnetic resonance imaging]] technology by which nanoscale images can be provided, that could enable researchers to peer into atomic structure of individual molecules.<ref>[http://phys.org/news/2014-04-mri-molecular-scale-team-peer.html MRI, on a molecular scale: Team develops system that could peer into atomic structure of individual molecules http://phys.org/news/2014-04-mri-molecular-scale-team-peer.html]</ref>

